JOHANNESBURG - Nearly a year after Karabo Mokoena was killed, allegedly by her ex-boyfriend, her family will hold a vigil in her memory in Soweto on Tuesday evening. The 23-year-old's burnt body was found dumped in a veld in Lyndhurst, Johannesburg in April 2017. Sandile Mantsoe is currently standing trial for her murder. Mantsoe denied killing Mokoena, claiming she may have committed suicide. Watch Mokoena's family and friends remembering her in the video above. eNCA